4 SYNOPSIS:
5
6 This bill would require athletic associations to
7 adjust a public high school's athletic classification
8 to reflect the number of English language learner
9 students who do not participate in athletics that are
10 enrolled at the school.
11
12
13 A BILL
14 TO BE ENTITLED
15 AN ACT
16
17 Relating to public high schools; to require athletic
18 associations to adjust schools' athletic classifications to
19 reflect enrolled English language learners who do not
20 participate in athletics.
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
22 Section 1. (a) For purposes of this section, the term
23 "athletic association" has the same meaning as provided in
24 Section 16-1-52.1, Code of Alabama 1975.
25 (b) Solely for purposes of classifying public high
26 schools for competition in athletic association championship
27 programs or other interscholastic athletic events, an athletic
28 association of which a public high school is a member shall
Page 1

association of which a public high school is a member shall
HB333 INTRODUCED
29 adjust the school's athletic classification to reflect the
30 number of English language learner students enrolled at the
31 school who do not participate in any interscholastic athletic
32 events.
33 (c) The State Board of Education shall adopt rules to
34 implement this section.
35 (d) This section shall apply beginning with the
36 athletic classifications in effect for the 2028-2029 academic
37 school year.
38 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
39 2026.
